      "page": "the devOps ways of work",
      "sentence": "UNIX and its discontentsBy the 1990s, I had learned enough that I felt ready to make my own contributions to this literature, writing on the benefits of symbolic interfaces, pioneering intranets as a way of delivering in-house software, touting infrastructure as code, describing generic client-server interfaces, stressing the basics of OOP, and more."
